voice_to_text: Here are a few things I'm gonna need as an anime fan when I grow up. No. 1 is kids. I don't mean buying them off the street, I mean, you know, my own kids that I can sit down, introduce them to anime, father son time, father daughter time, whatever time, and we can just sit and watch an anime like Overlord, cause I love Overlord. I really wanna introduce them to Overlord and just, you know, have a good time. Also, I would like a wife because, you know, kids kind of links up together. Doesn't matter if she's into anime or not, but, you know, preferably she is into anime or she's at least into like, Studio Ghibli films so you can watch them together, watch them with the kids. Whatever she would want to travel to, like, I don't know, the Studio Ghibli theme parks in Japan, or even just go to like, Croatia because of Paul Caruso or, you know, something like that. Flying over the Adriatic Sea or on a boat. I would love to do next is like a man cave. I don't really wanna call it that, but whatever. A room where I can put all my manga and which I will eventually buy, uh, books, novels, um, whatever, posters, DVDs, my Sonic Underground DVD and just kind of like, have that space where I can chill, my family can chill. Even if my, like, son or daughter brings friends around, they Can chill in there, you know, like a nice space. Pool table. I want it to be quite big. Mini fridge. Not asking for much, am I

voice_to_text: Hello, Robert Ramirez here. I am a professional voice actor. I've been doing this for about 10 years. I am not currently agent, however, I've been on a lot of projects and I've done a couple of commercials in my life. So, um, I would love to try to audition for your character if you haven't picked a voice actor yet. But your character looks amazing. I'd like to give it a try. Let's go. A lot people seem to think it's easy being a wizard. Pointy hat, staff, reptilian features. And you can conjure any little shiny object your heart desires. But these fools don't know the first thing about wizards. Wizardry takes decades to master, and you must be found pure of heart. Take myself, for example. I became a wizard to master the arcane arts. And because I look damn good in this hat. I once knew a wax wing who wanted to become a wizard. He Learned a spell to conjure fruit and ended up gorging himself on bubble berries. Greedy bastard. It's a shame, really. Not many of us have the self control it takes to resist the material pleasures magic can offer.
